    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-12-22T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-12-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="644"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d644">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/3377</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Military Attaché in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">McIlroy</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Adjutant General, United States Army</hi>
                        (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bridges</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="95" xml:id="d644fn95">Copy of telegram transmitted to the
                        Department by the War Department on December 22, 1931.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-12-22">December 22,
                            1931</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>No. 205. Japanese headquarters Mukden announces drive has begun on bandits west
                    of Liao River adding that anyone who interferes with this campaign will be
                    removed. Japanese General Staff Tokyo states: This force consisting of 2d
                    Division and 39th Brigade, former starting from south of Mukden, latter from
                    north of Mukden; this announcement is not an ultimatum, for if the Chinchow
                    force withdraws or does not resist, it will (Not) be molested.</p>
                <p>This office will be surprised if this movement does not end with all Liaoning
                    Province in the possession of the Japanese Army.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">McIlroy</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
